\begin_layout Definition
existential quantification, existential quantifier 
\begin_inset Formula $\exists$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
\begin_inset Separator plain
\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Remark*
A domain must always be specified when a statement 
\begin_inset Formula $\exists xP\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

 is used.
 Furthermore, the meaning of 
\begin_inset Formula $\exists xP\left(x\right)$
\end_inset

 changes when the domain changes.
 Without specifying the domain, the statement has no meaning.
 When all elements in the domain can be listed, the existential quantification
 is the same as the disjunction over the domain.
\end_layout

